 1991-05451991-03-220,  ,  CCAC,  , 
PrecisApproval of the appointment by the Minister of Consumer and Corporate Affairs of certain persons as members of the Standards Council of Canada to hold office during pleasure for a term of three years. (Mario Thériault, St-Jacques, New Brunswick, in the place of Dwight Hewlett, whose term has expired; Hervé Pomerleau, St-Georges, Quebec, in the place of Gerald Comeau, who has resigned; Jean Laflamme, Chicoutimi, Quebec, in the place of Madiha Kotb, whose term has expired; Jacques F. Bourassa, Sainte-Foy, Quebec, in the place of Hortense Michaud-Lalanne, who has resigned; Richard Schmidt, Dorion, Quebec, in the place of Claude Bourdon, whose term has expired; and Richard M. Muzyk, Winnipeg, Manitoba, in the place of Barry France, whose term has expired.
